        <ul style="list-style-type:disc">
            <li>
                The Tammattu Hajj consists of both ‘Umrah and Hajj; however, there is a break in between.
            </li>
            <li>
                In this type of hajj, the pilgrims make intention to enter into state of Ihram during the months of Hajj to perform ‘Umrah first. Once ‘Umrah is completed, then they are released from Ihram’s restrictions until Hajj.
            </li>
            <li>
                On or before 8th Dhul-hijja, prior to leaving Makkah for Mina, the pilgrims make intention and enter into state of Ihram again, this time to do Hajj only and perform all Hajj rituals.
            </li>

            <li>
                Those living in Makkah cannot perform this method of Hajj. 
                                 ذَألِكَ لِمَن لَّمۡ يَكُنۡ أَهۡلُهُ ۥ حَاضِرِى ٱلۡمَسۡجِدِ ٱلۡحَرَامِ‌... 
                    (...This is for those whose household is not in (the precincts of) the Sacred Mosque). (Surah Al-Baqarah, 2:196)

</li>
        </ul>


        
